[thinking] **Testing native support**
[thinking] 
[thinking] I’m thinking about writing a test, but I need to ensure Native unsupported catches are handled. The deftype/reify generates classes that might not be supported natively. The existing NewInstance catches could be useful. This test should verify if the compile works and handle failures due to unsupported dynamic class loading. I wonder whether I need to inspect generated deftype fields and how to best access them without using direct reflection. Using a function to create constants might be the way to go.
